def: The act of embroiling, or the condition of being embroiled;entanglement in a broil. Bp. Burnet.
The special cell in red algæ which produces or bears atrichogyne. See Illust. of Trichogyne.
The pincherlike claw of Crustacea and Arachnida.
In a doctrinal manner or for; by way of teaching or positivedirection.
Kindled of itself, or without extraneous aid or power. Dryden.
The quality of being arch; cleverness; sly humor free frommalice; waggishness. Goldsmith.
A machine generating more than one pressure wave; amultiphaser.
